06/03/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Prosecutors on Wednesday (March 5th) charged former Republika Srpska (RS) army commander Momir Savic with war crimes committed between April and September 1992 in Visegrad, eastern BiH. 
Savic is accused of persecuting Bosniak civilians while he was a member of a paramilitary unit of the Yugoslav National Army's Uzica Corps, as well as later, when he worked as commander of RS's Visegrad Brigade. 
He is charged with commanding, committing and participating in murder, deportation, imprisonment, torture and rape. 
(Beta, RTRS, SRNA, B92 - 05/03/08)
